stylometry: The concept of sensitivity analysis is really when you are changing one variable in the problem to find out how that will affect the rest of your conclusion.  For example, you have x cost when you sell item A and x cost when you sell item B, how many of each should you sell to maximize the profit, stay within the constraints, and take into concideration the cost of producing.  Once you get your answer you can run a sensitivity analysis to see how the outcome will change if your profit from producing A changed from $20 to $30, what will you produce of each product then?  This is important to you because you can see how much a little change can affect the profit margin, and could intern sway your decison.  Solver Table is a table that is set up so that when you change one thing on it it will affect the whole table.  When using this you can solve for several different things on that table.  Solver Table is improtant because in a business world cost, products, or set up costs may change and this will help you decide how it is that you want to run your business, or that part of your business, to maximize or minimize something in your company.
